* Install dependencies (sudo apt-get install python postgresql python-pip python-twisted python-psycopg2 python-dateutil python-openpyxl authbind python-ldap subversion cython gcc python2.7-dev pytz)
* cython -a scheme/symbol.pyx
* gcc -shared -pthread -fPIC -fwrapv -O2 -Wall -fno-strict-aliasing -I/usr/include/python2.7 -o scheme/symbol.so scheme/symbol.c
* cython -a scheme/processer.pyx
* gcc -shared -pthread -fPIC -fwrapv -O2 -Wall -fno-strict-aliasing -I/usr/include/python2.7 -o scheme/processer.so scheme/processer.c
*Start postgresql server (sudo /etc/init.d/postgresql start)
*Checkout django 1.8 [development version as of 8/2014] (svn checkout https://github.com/django/django.git/branches/stable/1.8.x ./django)
*Install django (sudo pip install -e django/)
*Configure authbind [see the authbind manual for instructions]
*create database in postgresql (sudo -u <postgresql_user_name> psql
	CREATE DATABASE <database_name>;
	CREATE ROLE <database_username> WITH LOGIN SUPERUSER ENCRYPTED PASSWORD '<database_user_password>';
	)
*Install first function in postgres (sudo -u postgres psql < firstsql)
*set database_name, database_username, database_user_password in settings.conf
*Apply migrations (python manage.py migrate)
*Create admin user (python manage.py createsuperuser)
** [Migrate old databases]
*start webserver (./startserver)


